        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 2:48AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>Temperatures remain around freezing across portions of the
Capital District, Mohawk Valley, Schoharie Valley and Helderbergs.
Some intermittent light freezing rain or drizzle may cause light
ice accumulations on colder untreated surfaces. Some slick spots
may be encountered on some roads or sidewalks.

Temperatures will start to rise back above freezing by daybreak
Sunday, as a warm front begins to move back northward across the
region, changing precipitation to plain rain or drizzle.
</description>
